sir jar file based on project




for string no need to declare TYPE
we no need to mention the type for varchar




Steps For Hibernate Pfoject :
1. Create the JAVA Project 
2. Create the /lib folder .
3. Place the Jar's file in to /lib folder [Total 14  Jars]
4. Select all the jar's and add to build path 
5. Place the file "hibernate.cfg.xml" in to /src folder *
	=> This file contain the configuration related to MySql DB Connection
	https://docs.jboss.org/hibernate/orm/3.3/reference/en/html/session-configuration.html
6. Create the POJO Class
7. Place the "*.hbm" file in to the same package where POJO Class are abalable 
8. HBM File name should be like - <POJO-CLASS-NAME>.hbm.xml
	
	
string Type in Hibernate ;
***************************
1. In hibernate STRING data Type denoted as "string"
2. Providing the data Types string is optional.




POJO Class
	Student.java
	
Entity Class or Persistance Class
	Student.java + Student.hbm.xml





*******START-StudentClient********* 
log4j:WARN No appenders could be found for logger (org.hibernate.cfg.Environment).
log4j:WARN Please initialize the log4j system properly.
---------1. Create the Configuration Object---------
---------2. Call the Configure Method---------
---------3. Through the COnfiguration Object call the Build Session Factory---------
---------4. With the factory object open the session---------
---------5. With the help of Session object begin the transaction ---------
---------6. Prepare the  Business Object ---------
---------7. Save the Data ---------
Hibernate: insert into STUDENT_DETAILS (STUDENT_NAME, STUDENT_EMAIL, STUDENT_PHONE, STUDENT_ID) values (?, ?, ?, ?)
---------8. Commit in to DB ---------
---------9. Close the Resourse ---------
*****END-StudentClient**** 




